==Old English==

===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*þwahljô'', from a Germanic base.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[þwahan]], Old High German [[dwahan]], Old Norse [[þvá]].  The Germanic base was also the source of English [[towel]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /θwæ:an/

===Verb===
'''þwēan''' (class VI strong: '''þweahþ''' ‘he washes’; '''þwōh''' ‘he washed’; '''þwōgon''' ‘they washed’; past participle '''ġeþwagen''')
# to [[wash]], [[anoint]]

